Bladder endometriosis in the patient after Caesarean section. Authors described a case of the endometriosis presence in the bladder wall in the patient who underwent the caesarean section. In this patient the appropriate surgery was executed. The bladder wall fragment containing the endometriosis focus was cut out. The period after surgery was uncomplicated. As the complementary efficace treatment the pharmacotherapy with Danol-Danazol was administered.